	     <form action="/cgi-bin/mrate.pl" name="f106382406672997">
	     <tr><td id="headerrow" colspan="2" class="mform" valign="top"><a id="sj" href="/db/item.html?item=23603&amp;mid=106382406672997">RE: points</a> <a id="fs8" href="/db/item.html?item=23603&amp;mid=106382406672997#post"><img src="/shared/reply_to_thread_ico.gif" border="0" alt="Reply..." width="17" height="11" /></a>
	     <br clear="all" /><small>Posted @ Wed, Sep 17th 2:44 PM 2003</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign="top" id="fs8" class="mform"><span id="notbold">By:</span> <a href="/db/poster.html?user=230099"><span id=" ">Quaranthalas</span></a><br /><span id="notbold">2 posts<br /><span id="notbold">Score</span>: Excellent [5.00]</td><td valign=top class="mform" width="100%"><p>The way I understand it is this: The game will keep track of how many points you have earned in each of the themes, and how many points you have currently, total.&nbsp;&nbsp;These numbers are not necessarily the same.  So, while you would have to initially earn 760 points in Miragul's in order to buy this breastplate, (or any of the other pieces in the set of the same name, I believe they all cost 760 points) the game would remember that you have earned 760 points in Miragul's, and all those things would still be available to buy, as long as you have the right number of points. Soooo, you could then go and earn 760 points in any of the other dungeons or any combination thereof, and then come back to Everfrost and get another piece of this armor set.  Basically, to get an item from a certain theme, you only have to earn the right number of that theme's points once, and thereafter you can use points from any theme, cuz the game remembers that you have already earned access to this item, and any others of the same point cost.<br/><br/>Perhaps a bit complicated to some, but I think I got the point across.</p>&nbsp;<br /></td></tr>
